PN,41202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1772554283
OL,3,C'Misfire' could have caused rifle to
OL,4,Cfire, killing soldier
OL,6,FColour Sergeant Gordon Smart, of 2
OL,7,FScots The Royal Regiment of Scotland,
OL,8,Ftold the Winchester inquest that he
OL,9,Fwas a safety supervisor on the day of
OL,10,Fthe fatal incident.
OL,12,FHe said L/Cpl Spencer was sheltering
OL,13,Ffrom the rain in an Iso shipping
OL,14,Fcontainer with colleagues as they
OL,15,Fwaited to go back on to the firing
OL,16,Frange when the fatal incident happened.
OL,18,FHe said that he heard shouts of "man
OL,19,Fdown" and ran to the shelter where he
OL,20,Ffound L/Cpl Spencer's body lying on
OL,21,Fthe floor with a rifle underneath him.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1772554283
OL,3,C'Misfire' could have caused rifle to
OL,4,Cfire, killing soldier
OL,6,FSgt Smart said one of the soldiers,
OL,7,FChristopher Leveridge, told him it was
OL,8,Fhis "fault" because he had bumped into
OL,9,Fhim.
OL,11,FHe said: "Everyone came out of the
OL,12,FIso, one of the students came out
OL,13,Fsaying 'That was my fault', sounds
OL,14,Fharsh but I kind of grabbed him and he
OL,15,Fsaid 'I bumped into him and then it
OL,16,Fwent off'.
OL,18,F"He was really white, shaking, just
OL,19,Fshock, I told him it wasn't his fault."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1772554283
OL,3,C'Misfire' could have caused rifle to
OL,4,Cfire, killing soldier
OL,6,FSgt Smart said that he had
OL,7,F"speculated" to police at the time
OL,8,Fthat a rifle could discharge a round
OL,9,Fwhen knocked if a round had "misfired"
OL,10,Fearlier.
OL,12,FHe explained that a "misfire" meant
OL,13,Fthat the firing pin had not struck the
OL,14,Fround properly, leaving the round in
OL,15,Fthe chamber, and said that if the
OL,16,Frifle was knocked in these
OL,17,Fcircumstances a round could be fired
OL,18,Fwithout the trigger being pulled.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1772554283
OL,3,C'Misfire' could have caused rifle to
OL,4,Cfire, killing soldier
OL,6,FHe said that a "misfire" where a round
OL,7,Fhad not been discharged had happened
OL,8,F"six or seven times" on the range but
OL,9,Fthe round was then ejected from the
OL,10,Fchamber by the soldier before carrying
OL,11,Fon with the exercise.
OL,13,FSgt Smart added that any misfired
OL,14,Fround should have been ejected from
OL,15,Fthe chamber by a soldier coming off
OL,16,Fthe range as they should carry out an
OL,17,F"unload drill" twice to ensure no
OL,18,Fbullets remained in the rifle.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1772554283
OL,3,C'Misfire' could have caused rifle to
OL,4,Cfire, killing soldier
OL,6,FSheriff Gary Aitken ruled in a fatal
OL,7,Faccident inquiry released in December
OL,8,F2024 that the incident was partly due
OL,9,Fto L/Cpl Spencer's "utterly
OL,10,Finexplicable failure" to unload his
OL,11,Frifle properly following a live fire
OL,12,Fexercise.
OL,14,FThe sheriff added that his death could
OL,15,Fhave been avoided if he had not been
OL,16,F"holding his rifle vertically in close
OL,17,Fproximity to his body during the
OL,18,Fundemanded discharge".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1772554283
OL,3,C'Misfire' could have caused rifle to
OL,4,Cfire, killing soldier
OL,6,FSheriff Aitken also pointed to
OL,7,Ffailures in the way the training
OL,8,Fcourse had been delivered, saying that
OL,9,Fif the "correct words of command to
OL,10,Fcarry out the unload drill" had been
OL,11,Fgiven, the incident could have been
OL,12,Favoided.
OL,14,FThe inquest, being heard by a jury of
OL,15,Ffive women and six men, continues.
OL,17,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,18,Four political experts are across all
OL,19,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,20,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/7
